Q10. follow up Question :
What is jagged array ?
in 2 dimentional array, 2nd dimension length is variable like,
        int[][] jagged = new int[3][]; // 3 rows

        jagged[0] = new int[]{1, 2};
        jagged[1] = new int[]{3, 4, 5};
        jagged[2] = new int[]{6};


Q11. follow up Question :
Write a program to input a square-matrix (2D array: rows & columns equals numbers = square-matrix)  and print the sum of left and right diagonal elements ?
Note: Diagonal elements :-
Diagonal ek line hoti hai jo matrix ke opposite corners ko join karti hai. 2D array ya square matrix me do main diagonals hote hain:
 a. left Diagonal
 b. right Diagonal.


                ‚Üì 0     ‚Üì 1    ‚Üì 2    ‚Üì 3      <- column
               ------------------------------
  rows -> 0    | (0,0)| (0,1)| (0,2)| (0,3) |   
               ------------------------------
  rows -> 1    | (1,0)| (1,1)| (1,2)| (1,3) |  
               ------------------------------
  rows -> 2    | (2,0)| (2,1)| (2,2)| (2,3) |
               ------------------------------
  rows -> 3    | (3,0)| (3,1)| (3,2)| (3,3) |
               ------------------------------
‚Üë\        / right Diagonal (row index + column index = total size - 1 ya i+j==n-1)                 
   \     /
    \   /
     \ / 
      X
     / \
    /   \
   /     \
 ‚Üì/       \ left Diagonal ( row index = column index ya i==j)

Example :
-> rows and columns of 2 * 2 
-> add elements : 4,5,3,1
-> leftDiagonalSum = 5
-> rightDiagonalSum = 8


